git vbranch [<options>] [--] <branch> [<at>] - Create a new vbranch and its vnode.

    -h|--help               display help
    --push                  Push vbranch and vnode
    -m|--message VALUE      Tag message (default to <at> message)
    <branch>                Vbranch name (ex: 1.0)
    <at>                    Vbranch and vnode location (default to HEAD)
    
example:
    git vbranch 1.0                 # create vbranch 1.0 and vnode v1.0-@ at HEAD
    git vbranch --push 1.0 <SHA1>   # create vbranch 1.0 and vnode v1.0-@ at <SHA1> and push
